items.title: Porcupine
items.description:
Dan King Alaskan Photography posted a photo:

My wife and I were headed down the Alaska Highway and stopped at the Gerstle River to stretch our legs and water our dog. While my wife and dog were walking along the bank of the river, I went into the woods on a small trail. To my surprise and delight, a big porcupine was walking down the trail towards me. Since my camera was in hand, I decided to put it to use and took some photos.
What I thought was very cool, is that the Porcupine just kept walking towards me. When he was about 15 feet away, he finally noticed me and scurried off the trail. I didn't go after him for more photos because the brush was thick and I didn't want to harass him.
It's chance encounters with wildlife that I love, unexpected and spontaneous. This is the reason I travel all the time with my camera on my lap.
items.author: nobody@flickr.com ("Dan King Alaskan Photography")
